Confessions of the Mind is the 1970 released album by The Hollies. It was released in the United States as Moving Finger, with a different track sequence, the track "I Wanna Shout" omitted and replaced with the Clarke/Sylvester penned "Marigold: Gloria Swansong" saved from the previous album (Hollies Sing Hollies aka He Ain't Heavy, He's My Brother - U.S.). In Germany, it was released as The Hollies Move On. The UK version peaked at UK #30. The US version peaked at US #21.

Please note that the album title reads Confessions of the Mind, while the title track (track #06) is called "Confessions of a Mind".
